      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Drakent wrote:</div><div class="orig">Everything that was writing down on why goin back to  Final Fantasy XI is misleading by a fan of Final Fantasy XI but the true is that i wouldnt recomend any mmo player to start playing Final Fantasy XI  or even try to come back to it.  the True is this  <br /> <br /> Is it too late to join?  <br />    <br />The lie  <br />(No, it's never too late. As with most MMOs, there will be a population that is already much higher in level than you. Unlike most MMOs, this doesn't matter nearly as much, as you cannot be killed by fellow players. This allows you to catch up to those already at the level cap without detriment. )  <br /> <br />The true <br />The leveling system on this game is 1 of the most time-consuming that any mmo has, to level up require a group of 6 members  tank healer 3 DD or dps and 1 suport job,  if you may ask whats a suport job is a class that increases others  classes performence. If you are new in the game and dont have any friends you gona have a few problems   <br /> <br />1)it could take you from 30min to a few Hrs to find a group to lvl up  <br /> <br />2)on this game you have a sub job wich is where you combine the ability of  your main job with a nother like  warrior/ninja but to be able to do this you need to collect some items frome monsters that cant be done alone wich mean you would have to go around beging for some 1 to help you since finding help in this game aint easy <br /> <br />3)Do the fact that you dont have a sub job until lvl 18 most player will be discouraged to invite you to a group making it longer for you to find a party to lvl up. <br /> <br />4)There a lvl cap onces you hit that cap you require to pick some items frome a quest that will give you acces  to lvl up once again, good luck finding a hand this could take you a few hrs or days to do and you have to do this quest 3 different times.  <br /> <br />5)To get acces to some location in the game so you can lvl up require for you todo some quest that will give you the acces to  does lvling spot or what the games calls camping spot. again this  will require helps frome other players ...more beging to do.  <br /> <br />if you the type of player that  only plays for 3-5hr a day it could take you 4 to 6 months to be able to hit 75 wich the max lvl. In other mmo the most time you would spend lvling up would be 1 to 2 months to hit the max lvl     <br /> <br /> <br />How is the economy?  <br /> <br /> <br />While it does vary from server to server, overall the economy has deflated a lot from the heights it reached. With the aggressive actions of the Special Task Force, gilsellers have been banned in huge amounts. And while they still exist, they do not exist to the degree that they did.  <br /> <br />The reality!  <br />Final Fantasy XI  has the worst economy in any mmo actually more like its the only mmo with bad economy and is the main reason this game losses players to others mmo. <br />A new player that plays 3-5hr a day will spend 2-3 days farming gold for about every 10-15 lvl you hit so you could upgrade you armor. this makes  players end up doing two thing  <br /> <br />1) they quit the game  <br />2) they like the game so much that they buy gold for reall $ so they can keep playing  <br /> <br /> <br />Is Final Fantasy XI dying?  <br /> <br />Short answer: No.  <br /> <br />reality!! <br />yes the game is slowly coming to its end. <br />reason why? the game every years loses numbers of player little by little to the point where square enix will be spending money to keep the game up instead of making money  this is why they are  making a  new mmo instead of adding a new expansion they are gona try all over again since ffxi is not meeting there expectation. If you read on the new ff mmo they are actually makig it similar to other mmo when it comes down to being time-consuming. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />The only people who are still playing ffxi are 2 types.  <br /> <br />1)the onces that spend so much time in the game and gotten so far that they just cant drop all that hard work. this group of ppl will quit the game onces the new ff mmo comes out.  <br /> <br />2)Hardcore player, ffxi is the only mmo game that you are able to stand out frome other player. There are gears on this game that takes so many years to get wich only hardcore player are able to get. carrying this gears would make you a godly player to the point where your name would be know to every 1 on that server.  This type of player wont quit until the game is shutdown  <br />     <br /> <br />    <br />  <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec 11th 2009 11:20pm by Drakent</span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec 11th 2009 11:20pm by Drakent</span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Dec 11th 2009 11:22pm by Drakent</span></i></div></div> <br /> <br />One sided opinion how crappy and very misleading.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>&lt;3My Beautiful daughter&lt;3     ~9/26/2007~ <br />Ex Army Gal 68W &amp; 92G hoah <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">jtftaru wrote:</div><div class="orig">The Internet is full of nasty, snide little turds who (often in little cliques) use the anonymity of the Internet to manifest their unpleasant personalities towards others.</div></div></div></div>
