      <div class="msgContentFrame">I played ffxi for roughly 3 years march 2005 till nov 2007. I didnt pay much attention towards the end of the game. I was a 75sam with most of the other jobs at 37. I joined alot of linkshells to try and do dynamis and the AOU missions.  <br /> <br />Game got quite boring. <br /> <br />After i had left they introduced levelsync which i thought was alot of rubbish because the main aspect of levelling in FFXI is to have a well balanced party that will at least spend 8 hours in the one area advancing 4-5 levels if you are lucky. Hearing that it is possible to solo to 75 makes me want to join again instantly. End game has also been made more interesting with mythic weapons and campaign (solo stuff). And not to forget the latest expansion wings of the godess with the 2 play on scenarios.  <br /> <br />Personally im going to start back up possibly early next year. <br /> <br />But i do reccomend anyone who quit during or before the ToAU expansion for any reason such as LFG for hours, or end game boredom or drama within an endgame LS. Im assuming that the game has changed alot due to the solo add ons. <br /> <br /></div>
